nce of opinion. That is not easy! My view is that, just one year ago,=C2=A0=
Bankman-Fried <em>really was good at getting attention and investors</em>, =
and in a way that=C2=A0<em>could=C2=A0</em>play well in court: He was not o=
bviously slick and outgoing and charming, but rather had a sort of nebbishy=
 charm that came across as being candid and awkward. No version of charm is=
