<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elon Musk wants X to be the center of your fin=
ancial world, handling anything in your life that deals with money. He expe=
cts those features to launch by the end of 2024, he told X employees during=
 an all-hands call on Thursday, saying that people will be surprised with =
=E2=80=9Cjust how powerful it is.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWhen I say payments, I actually mean =
someone=E2=80=99s entire financial life,=E2=80=9D Musk said, according to a=
udio of the meeting obtained by The Verge. =E2=80=9CIf it involves money. I=
t=E2=80=99ll be on our platform. Money or securities or whatever. So, it=E2=
=80=99s not just like send $20 to my friend. I=E2=80=99m talking about, lik=
e, you won=E2=80=99t need a bank account.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The original plan for X.com is clearly on Musk=
=E2=80=99s mind. =E2=80=9CThe X/PayPal product roadmap was written by mysel=
f and David Sacks actually in July of 2000,=E2=80=9D Musk said on Thursday=
=E2=80=99s internal X call. =E2=80=9CAnd for some reason PayPal, once it be=
came eBay, not only did they not implement the rest of the list, but they a=
ctually rolled back a bunch of key features, which is crazy. So PayPal is a=
ctually a less complete product than what we came up with in July of 2000, =
so 23 years ago.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Imagine if Twitter/X becomes the center of the=
 financial world by the end of next year. The joke will really be on me.=C2=
=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also I still do not understand why Elon Musk s=
pent $44 billion to buy Twitter to turn it into Vintage Paypal? Why not buy=
 =E2=80=A6=C2=A0I mean literally PayPal Holdings Inc. has an equity market =
capitalization of about $56 billion today; that=E2=80=99s more than $44 bil=
lion, but it also has earnings before interest, taxes depreciation and amor=
tization of more than $5 billion a year, so he could probably have gotten s=
ome banks to lend him more of the money. Robinhood Markets Inc. has an $8 b=
illion market capitalization and a meme-y audience of people who already tr=
ust it with their money, which is just extremely not true of Twitter. There=
 are financial technology startups that are positively cheap! Or you can st=
art one! Buying Twitter to (1) get rid of its employees, (2) get rid of its=
 name and branding and (3) pivot to payments seems bizarrely profligate.</p=
>
